The folder contains the original manuals for the package written in CBasic.
This is Inventory Control System manual and a Separate Specifications manual.

It was written to use a word processor from the 80's using CPM.
The tool details I cannot remember BUT the files can be inserted into a Open
Document format document using Insert Text as used by LO (LibreOffice) and MS
word after 2019 (as far as I know - No I have never tested this as I cannot
afford to buy MS products and even less so when LibreOffice is free to get and
use.

I have created a manual for the Payroll package using LO using the same method
creating the .ODF file and from that the PDF document but it did take me some
four hours of work.  If I have them time I will create similar for this but very
basic and let you add the missing text such as a Title page and a Contents page.
I have found printed copies of these two manuals so subject to free time will
attempt to create them using the files in this folder.

I have now created the Inventory (IY) manual producing a .PDF file but took
longer than anticipated - so what else is new?.


